department /dɪˈpɑːtmənt/

(departments) 

1. N-COUNT A department is one of the sections in an organization such as a government, business, or university. A department is also one of the sections in a large shop. (政府、企业等机构的) 部; (大学的) 系; (大型商店的) 部门 

例： ...the U.S. Department of Health and Human Services. …美国健康和公共事业部。 

例： He moved to the sales department. 他调到了销售部。

